blocks.tex:
Additivity and $\mathcal{D}$-homogeneity in the direction slot follow from
  the corresponding laws of $\overline{
abla}$ and of the projection
  (\cref{lem:dc-ch6-2-proj}). For the Leibniz rule,
  $\overline{
abla}_X(fY)=f\overline{
abla}_XY+X(f)\,Y$; taking tangential
  parts, the term $X(f)\,Y$ is already tangent, giving
  $
abla_X(fY)=f
abla_XY+X(f)\,Y$. For symmetry, the difference
  $\overline{
abla}_XY-\overline{
abla}_YX=[X,Y]$ is tangent for tangent
  $X,Y$ (\cref{def:dc-ch6-2-patch}(ii)), so applying the projection gives
  $
abla_XY-
abla_YX=[X,Y]$. For compatibility, write
  $\overline{
abla}_XY=(\overline{
abla}_XY)^T+(\overline{
abla}_XY)^N$ in
  $X\langle Y,Zangle
  =\langle\overline{
abla}_XY,Zangle+\langle Y,\overline{
abla}_XZangle$;
  the normal parts pair to zero against the tangent fields $Z$ and $Y$.

blocks.body:
The \emph{second fundamental form} of the patch is
  $B(X,Y)=\overline{
abla}_XY-
abla_XY=(\overline{
abla}_XY)^N$, a
  normal-valued form on fields, giving the \emph{Gauss decomposition}
  $\overline{
abla}_XY=
abla_XY+B(X,Y)$.

