blocks.tex:
Substitute the Gauss decomposition
  $\overline{
abla}_XW=
abla_XW+B(X,W)$ (\cref{def:dc-ch6-2-B}) and the
  Weingarten decomposition
  $\overline{
abla}_X\eta=-S_\eta(X)+
abla^\perp_X\eta$
  (\cref{def:dc-ch6-3-normal-connection}) into
  $\overline{R}(X,Y)W=\overline{
abla}_Y\overline{
abla}_XW
  -\overline{
abla}_X\overline{
abla}_YW+\overline{
abla}_{[X,Y]}W$ and
  collect terms: for the first identity split
  $\overline{
abla}_XZ=
abla_XZ+B(X,Z)$, then split
  $\overline{
abla}_Y(
abla_XZ)=
abla_Y
abla_XZ+B(Y,
abla_XZ)$ and
  $\overline{
abla}_Y(B(X,Z))=-S_{B(X,Z)}Y+
abla^\perp_YB(X,Z)$, and likewise
  for the terms with $X$ and $Y$ interchanged and for
  $\overline{
abla}_{[X,Y]}Z$; for the second identity split
  $\overline{
abla}_X\eta=-S_\eta(X)+
abla^\perp_X\eta$, then
  $\overline{
abla}_Y(S_\eta X)=
abla_Y(S_\eta X)+B(Y,S_\eta X)$ and
  $\overline{
abla}_Y(
abla^\perp_X\eta)
  =-S_{
abla^\perp_X\eta}Y+
abla^\perp_Y
abla^\perp_X\eta$, and likewise for
  the remaining terms.

